This paper focuses on self-supervised learning of visual representations, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentations and nonlinear transformations, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of larger batch sizes and more training steps, which are relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
